Gov Samuel Ortom of the People’s Democratic Party (PDP), is edging towards victory with 317,730 votes from the results of the Governorship polls  so far released in 19 Local Government Areas of Benue State. The results were announced by different Collation Officers for the local government areas in Makurdi. The INEC records show that Mr. Emmanuel Jime of the All Progressives Congress (APC), has polled 264,505 votes, lagging behind with 53,225 votes. Results from Vandeikya, Buruku, Kwande and Konshisha Local governments are yet to be declared.